		<content type="html" xml:base="https://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=259101#p259101"><![CDATA[
<blockquote class="uncited"><div><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>-- By Pedro Gimeno, donated to the public domainfunction isPointInPolygon(x, y, poly)  local x1, y1, x2, y2  local len = #poly  x2, y2 = poly[len - 1], poly[len]  local wn = 0  for idx = 1, len, 2 do    x1, y1 = x2, y2    x2, y2 = poly[idx], poly[idx + 1]    if y1 &gt; y then      if (y2 &lt;= y) and (x1 - x) * (y2 - y) &lt; (x2 - x) * (y1 - y) then        wn = wn + 1      end    else      if (y2 &gt; y) and (x1 - x) * (y2 - y) &gt; (x2 - x) * (y1 - y) then        wn = wn - 1      end    end  end  return wn % 2 ~= 0 -- even/odd ruleend</code></pre></div>Second edit: fix a boundary condition</div></blockquote>I have this code bellow for check if have npc is inside polygon...work nice, but possible improve this code? performance?<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>function InsideZone(x,y,poly)if (x ~= nil) and (y ~= nil) and (poly ~= nil) thenn = #poly;inside = false;p1x,p1y = poly[1].X, poly[1].Yp2x,p2y = (poly[n].X),(poly[n].Y)if y &gt; math.min(p1y,p2y) thenif y &lt;= math.max(p1y,p2y) thenif x &lt;= math.max(p1x,p2x) thenif p1y ~= p2y thenxinters = (y-p1y)*(p2x-p1x)/(p2y-p1y)+p1xend;if p1x == p2x or x &lt;= xinters theninside = not insideend;end;end;end;for i=1,n-1 dop2x,p2y = (poly[i+1].X),(poly[i+1].Y)if y &gt; math.min(p1y,p2y) thenif y &lt;= math.max(p1y,p2y) thenif x &lt;= math.max(p1x,p2x) thenif p1y ~= p2y thenxinters = (y-p1y)*(p2x-p1x)/(p2y-p1y)+p1xend;if p1x == p2x or x &lt;= xinters theninside = not insideend;end;end;end;p1x,p1y = p2x,p2yend;return inside;end;end;</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=217612">maneco2</a> — Sat Mar 23, 2024 6:01 pm</p><hr />
